{"title_page": "TVR Chimaera", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2017}}\n{{Use British English|date=July 2017}}\n\n{{More citations needed|date=April 2018}}\n\n{{Infobox automobile\n| image        = Black TVR Chimaera.jpg\n| caption = TVR Chimaera 500\n| name         = TVR Chimaera\n| manufacturer = [[TVR|TVR Motor Company]]\n| assembly = [[Blackpool]], [[England]]\n| production   = 1992\u20132003\n| predecessor  = \n| successor    = [[TVR Tamora]]\n| class        = [[Sports car]] \n| body_style   = 2-door [[convertible (car)|convertible]]\n| engine       = 4.0 L [[Rover Group|Rover]] [[V8 engine|V8]]<br>4.3 L [[Rover Group|Rover]] [[V8 engine|V8]]<br>4.5 L [[Rover Group|Rover]] [[V8 engine|V8]]<br>5.0 L [[Rover Group|Rover]] [[V8 engine|V8]] (Chimaera 500 models only)\n| related      = [[TVR Griffith]]\n| wheelbase = {{cvt|2286|mm|in|1|abbr=on}}<ref name=\"sp\">{{cite web|url=https://www.carfolio.com/specifications/models/car/?car=30492#a_dimensions|title= TVR Chimaera specifications|accessdate= 3 February 2018}}</ref>\n| length = {{cvt|4015|mm|in|1|abbr=on}}<ref name=\"sp\"/>\n| width = {{cvt|1865|mm|in|1|abbr=on}}<ref name=\"sp\"/>\n| height = {{cvt|1215|mm|in|1|abbr=on}}<ref name=\"sp\"/>\n| weight       = {{Convert|1060|kg|lb|0|abbr=on}}\n}}\n\nThe '''TVR Chimaera''' is a two-seater [[convertible (car)|convertible]] [[sports car]] manufactured by [[TVR (car)|TVR]] between 1992 and 2003. The name was derived from [[Chimera (mythology)|Chimera]], the monstrous creature of [[Greek mythology]], which was made of the parts of multiple animals.\n\nThe car used the same backbone chassis as the [[TVR Griffith|Griffith]] and used the same derivatives of the [[Rover V8]] engine.\n\nThe Chimaera was intended to be the long distance tourer of the range and as such was longer, more spacious and had slightly softer suspension than its sister car.\n\n==Specifications==\n===Engine===\n*90 degree aluminium V8\n\nAll engines are based on the 3.5 L [[Rover V8 engine|Rover V8]] unit, with increased cylinder capacity.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" cellpadding=\"0\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size:91%;\"\n|-\n!Model\n!Capacity (cc)\n!Power\n!Torque\n!Max speed\n!0-{{convert|60|mph|km/h|abbr=on}} (s)\n!0-{{convert|100|mph|0|abbr=on}} (s)\n|-\n|4.0||3,950 V8|| {{convert|240|bhp|kW PS|0|abbr=on}} ||{{convert|270|lbft|Nm|0|abbr=on}} at 4000 rpm||{{convert|152|mi/h|km/h|abbr=on}}||5.1||12.5\n|-\n|4.0 HC||3,950 Hi Compression V8|| {{convert|275|bhp|kW PS|0|abbr=on}} ||{{convert|305|lbft|Nm|0|abbr=on}}||{{convert|158|mi/h|km/h|abbr=on}}||4.7||12.1\n|-\n|4.3||4,280 V8|| {{convert|280|bhp|kW PS|0|abbr=on}} ||{{convert|305|lbft|Nm|0|abbr=on}} at 4000 rpm||{{convert|158|mi/h|km/h|abbr=on}}||4.6||11.3\n|-\n|4.5||4,546 V8|| {{convert|285|bhp|kW PS|0|abbr=on}} ||{{convert|310|lbft|Nm|0|abbr=on}}||{{convert|160|mi/h|0|abbr=on}}||4.7||11.2\n|-\n|5.0||4,988 V8|| {{convert|340|bhp|kW PS|0|abbr=on}} ||{{convert|320|lbft|Nm|0|abbr=on}}||{{convert|175|mi/h|km/h|abbr=on}}||4.1||10.2\n|}\n\n===Suspension===\nThe suspension consisted of all round independent, unequal-length double wishbones and coil over gas dampers assisted by anti-roll bars. Ground clearance was about {{Convert|5|in}}.\n\n===Braking===\nThe front disc brakes were {{convert|239|mm|in||abbr=on}} on smaller displacement cars, and {{convert|260|mm|in||abbr=on}} diameter and ventilated on five litre models. The rear disc brakes were {{convert|253|mm|in||abbr=on}}, or {{convert|273|mm|in||abbr=on}} in diameter on the five litre model. Both sets were servo assisted with front/rear split dual circuits. There was a cable-operated hand brake for the rear wheels.\n\n===Steering===\n*Steering was optionally power-assisted and worked via rack and pinion with adjustable steering column.\n*There were 2.2 turns lock to lock for the power-assisted steering or 2.5 for unassisted.\n*The steering wheel was {{convert|350|mm|in||abbr=on}} in diameter and leather-covered, although other wheels could be specified by the customer. The standard fit was by Personal, in keeping with a majority of TVR models.\n\n===Manufacturer's options===\n*Power assisted steering\n*Air conditioning\n*Rear speakers\n*Six CD autochanger\n*Full leather\n*Heated Seats\n*Wood and Chrome Steering Wheel\n*Wool Carpets\n*Gold coloured badges\n*Seven spoke 'Griffith 500' wheels for smaller engine versions (standard on 5.0)\n*4,988 cc V8 (5.0) initially a factory option on the 4.3 and 4.5 litre models\n\n==Additional images==\n<gallery>\nFile:Chimaera-Interior.jpg|Interior of Chimaera 500 1998\nFile:Chimaera500.JPG|1998 Chimaera 500\nFile:TVR Chimaera rear.jpg|Rear of Chimaera\n</gallery>\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|TVR Chimaera}}\n*[http://www.chimaerapages.com TVR Chimaera Pages - A guide to ownership and maintenance of the TVR Chimaera. Includes a gallery of pictures.]\n*[http://www.pistonheads.com/tvr/chimaera/review.htm TVR Chimaera review on Pistonheads]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20060620031125/http://www.chimaerapages.com/resources_buyers.php TVR Chimaera buyer's guide]\n*[http://users.firenet.uk.com/martinjones/tvr.htm  TVR Chimaera pictures, specifications etc.]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20140517044743/http://chimaera500.com/ - TVR Chimaera 500 site, Includes a gallery of pictures & video.]\n{{TVR}}\n{{TVR road car timeline}}\n\n[[Category:TVR vehicles|Chimaera]]\n[[Category:Sports cars]]\n[[Category:Rear-wheel-drive vehicles]]\n[[Category:Coup\u00e9s]]\n[[Category:2000s cars]]\n[[Category:Cars introduced in 1992]]\n[[Category:Automobiles with backbone chassis]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2017}}\n{{Use British English|date=July 2017}}\n\n{{More citations needed|date=April 2018}}\n\n{{Infobox automobile\n| image        = Black TVR Chimaera.jpg\n| caption = TVR Chimaera 500\n| name         = TVR Chimaera\n| manufacturer = [[TVR|TVR Motor Company]]\n| assembly = [[Blackpool]], [[England]]\n| production   = 1992\u20132003\n| pr